Serialized Form

  • Package com.dropbox.core

    • Class com.dropbox.core.DbxAppInfo extends Dumpable implements Serializable

      serialVersionUID:
      0L

      • Serialized Fields

        • key

          String key
          Your Dropbox app key (OAuth calls this the consumer key). You can create an app key and secret on the Dropbox developer website.

        • secret

          String secret
          Your Dropbox app secret (OAuth calls this the consumer secret). You can create an app key and secret on the Dropbox developer website.

          Make sure that this is kept a secret. Someone with your app secret can impesonate your application. People sometimes ask for help on the Dropbox API forums and copy/paste their code, which sometimes includes their app secret. Do not do that.

        • host

          DbxHost host
          This is almost always DbxHost.Default. This is only set differently for testing purposes.

    • Class com.dropbox.core.DbxAuthFinish extends Object implements Serializable

      serialVersionUID:
      0L

      • Serialized Fields

        • accessToken

          String accessToken
          An access token that can be used to make Dropbox API calls. Pass this in to the DbxClient constructor.

        • userId

          String userId
          The Dropbox user ID of the user who just approved your app for access to their Dropbox account.

        • urlState

          String urlState
          The state data you passed in to DbxWebAuth.start(java.lang.String). If you didn't pass anything in, or you used DbxWebAuthNoRedirect, this will be null.

    • Class com.dropbox.core.DbxEntry extends Dumpable implements Serializable

      serialVersionUID:
      0L

      • Serialized Fields

        • name

          String name
          Just the last part of DbxEntry.path. Derived automatically from DbxEntry.path.
          See Also:
          DbxPath.getName(java.lang.String)

        • path

          String path
          The path to the file or folder, relative to your application's root. The path always starts with a "/".

          For full-Dropbox apps, the path is relative to the root of the user's Dropbox. For App Folder apps, the path is relative to your application's App Folder within the user's Dropbox.

        • iconName

          String iconName
          The name of the icon to use for this file. The set of names returned by this call match up with icons in a set of icons provided by Dropbox. Read more about the icon field in Dropbox's documentation for the /metadata HTTP endpoint.

        • mightHaveThumbnail

          boolean mightHaveThumbnail
          Whether this file or folder might have a thumbnail image you can retrieve via the DbxClient.getThumbnail call. If this is true, there might be a thumbnail available. If this is false, there is definitely no thumbnail available.

    • Class com.dropbox.core.DbxEntry.File extends DbxEntry implements Serializable

      serialVersionUID:
      0L

      • Serialized Fields

        • numBytes

          long numBytes
          The size, in bytes, of the file content.

        • humanSize

          String humanSize
          A human-readable string version of the file size (ex: "13 kb"). This string will be localized based on the Locale in DbxRequestConfig.userLocale (passed in to the DbxClient constructor).

        • lastModified

          Date lastModified
          The time the file was added, moved, or last had it's contents changed on the Dropbox server. (This probably won't match the time on the Dropbox user's filesystem. For that the DbxEntry.File.clientMtime is a better estimate.)

        • clientMtime

          Date clientMtime
          The modification time sent up by the Dropbox desktop client when the file was added or modified. This time is based on the system clock of the particular host that the client was running on, as opposed to the system clock of the Dropbox servers.

          This field should not be used to determine if a file has changed, but only as a way to sort files by date (when displaying a list of files to the user).

        • rev

          String rev
          The revision of the file at this path. This can be used with DbxClient.uploadFile(java.lang.String, com.dropbox.core.DbxWriteMode, long, java.io.InputStream) and the DbxWriteMode.update(java.lang.String) mode to make sure you're overwriting the revision of the file you think you're overwriting.

        • photoInfo

          DbxEntry.File.PhotoInfo photoInfo
          If this file is a photo, this may contain additional photo-related information. This field is only populated if you use the includeMediaInfo

        • videoInfo

          DbxEntry.File.VideoInfo videoInfo
          Contains details about this file if it is a video

    • Class com.dropbox.core.DbxEntry.WithChildren extends Dumpable implements Serializable

      serialVersionUID:
      0L

      • Serialized Fields

        • entry

          DbxEntry entry
          The metadata for the base file or folder.

        • hash

          String hash
          If DbxEntry.WithChildren.entry is a folder, this will contain a hash that identifies the folder's contents. This value can be used with DbxClient.getMetadataWithChildrenIfChanged(java.lang.String, boolean, java.lang.String) to void downloading the folder contents if they havne't changed.

        • children

          List<E> children
          If DbxEntry.WithChildren.entry is a folder, this will contain the metadata of the folder's immediate children. If it's not a folder, this will be null.

    • Class com.dropbox.core.DbxHost extends Object implements Serializable

      serialVersionUID:
      0L

      • Serialized Fields

        • api

          String api
          The host name of the main Dropbox API server. The default is "api.dropbox.com".

        • content

          String content
          The host name of the Dropbox API content server. The default is "api-content.dropbox.com".

        • web

          String web
          The host name of the Dropbox web server. Used during user authorization. The default is "www.dropbox.com".

        • notify

          String notify
          The host name of the Dropbox notification server. Used by the /longpoll_delta API. The default is "api-notify.dropbox.com".
